.TH DEVPULSE 1 "2026-06-29" "DevCore 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
devpulse \- developer workflow analyzer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B devpulse
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
DevPulse monitors your development workflow and generates reports showing exactly where time is spent: coding, reviewing, searching, building, or context-switching.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init [\-\-path PATH]
Initialize DevPulse in the current project.
.TP
.B report [\-\-period PERIOD] [\-\-path PATH]
Generate a workflow report for a time period.
.I PERIOD
can be
.BR day ,
.BR week ,
or
.BR month .
.TP
.B event \-k KIND \-m MINUTES [\-d DESCRIPTION] [\-\-path PATH]
Record a manual event. KIND is one of:
.BR coding ,
.BR review ,
.BR build ,
.BR search ,
.BR meeting ,
.BR ai .
.TP
.B suggest [\-\-path PATH]
Show suggestions for reducing time waste based on recent activity.
.TP
.B chart [\-\-period PERIOD] [\-\-path PATH]
Show time breakdown as a visual chart by hour of day.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " PATH
Project root directory (default: current directory).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .devcore/devcore.db
SQLite database storing workflow events.
.SH SEE ALSO
shipforge(1), codetrail(1)
